Quote: Amongst the practical measures ... for the protection of the aborigines, the most important are, the support of the missions and the missionaries ... [28] The official protection of the aborigines will be committed to one principal officer ... The general duty of protector would be to watch over the execution of the laws, in ... the rights and interests of the natives; ...
Notes: 1840 Dec 9 Lord John Russell to Governor Hobson in GBPP House of Commons 1841 (No.311) 27

