Quote: All such [land-purchase] contracts should be made by yourself, through the intervention of an Officer expressly appointed to watch over the interests of the Aborigines as their Protector. [FN] Created 1840 abolished at end of first quarter of 1846 by Grey. Grey to Stanley 10 May 1846 CO 209/43 P.137 -[FN] Created 1840 abolished at end of first quarter of 1846 by Grey. Grey to Stanley 10 May 1846 CO 209/43 P.137 -[FN] Created 1840 abolished at end of first quarter of 1846 by Grey. Grey to Stanley 10 May 1846 CO 209/43 P.137 <i>Ibid.</i> 16 Amongst the Officers thus to be created, the most evidently indispensable are those of a Judge, a Public Prosecutor, a Protector of Aborigines, a Colonial Secretary, a Treasurer, a Surveyor General of Lands, and a Superintendent of Police.
